
[1]fashionable

   FASH'IONABLE, a.

   1. Made according to the prevailing form or mode; as a fashionable
   dress.

   2. Established by custom or use; current; prevailing at a particular
   time; as the fashionable philosophy; fashionable opinions.

   3. Observant of the fashion or customary mode; dressing or behaving
   according to the prevailing fashion; as a fashionable man. Hence,

   4. Genteel; well bred; as fashionable company or society.
